marked: TMT time and regional cerebral blood flow (rCBF) using SPECT data.
As a first step, we investigated the cerebral correlates of the TMT-A
study, we aimed to compare the rCBF of AD patients with good and poor performances on the TMT-A, and to investigate the neural substrate involved in the performance of AD patients on the TMT-A.
Eighteen AD patients with dementia severity of 0.5 (suspicious) or 1 (mild) based on the CDR
were examined by brain perfusion SPECT

We predicted hypoperfusion in the parietal region among AD patients with poor performance on the TMT-A, and this study revealed that rCBF in the bilateral superior parietal lobule of AD patients with poor performance on the TMT-A was lower than that of AD patients with good performance on the TMT-A.
